# Netlify header rules — never cache the HTML pages. Without this, a fix
# pushed to main can keep showing the OLD broken page to real visitors
# (browser cache and/or Netlify's CDN cache) even though the source is fixed,
# which reads as "I just fixed it and it's still broken."
/*.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate
/
  Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate
